Question:
What is the average expected loss provision in NOK for corporate clients with gross exposure subject to collateral hair-down and with credit spreads reweighted using a Gaussian kernel across tenors?

Restrict the calculation to:

1) overnight indexed swap spline with local interpolation at 2-year tenor, variation margining only including collateral substitution, and commodity price collapse scenario;

2) overnight indexed swap spline anchored at 3-month forward-start tenor, initial margin plus variation margin with segregated collateral, and global GDP contraction scenario;

3) overnight indexed swap spline with log-linear extrapolation beyond 10-year tenor, daily margining with procyclical threshold adjustments, and oil supply disruption scenario?
